Elizabeth “Liz” Moyano is a nurse and director of quality and performance improvement at St. Mary’s General Hospital in Passaic, New Jersey, fighting coronavirus on the front lines.
“Like many hospitals, we are working through many staffing issues and supply issues,” she says.
The stresses of fighting COVID-19 have not stopped Moyano from pursuing her goals: Each night before bed, she does her homework for her Master of Nursing administration and leadership class.
“I have not stopped to think or attempted to cope with the exhaustion.
“The thing that keeps me going, truly, is seeing all the COVID patients that recover and being discharged home.